{% if include_stream_runtime and include_redis_plugin %}
## Stream Runtime

The FastStream runtime lives in `{{ package_name }}/runtimes/stream/`.

The current stream scaffold uses the Redis integration as its broker transport.
It is assembled explicitly from `app.py`, `lifecycle.py`, and task routers under `runtimes/stream/tasks/`.
The runtime also provides `build_asgi_app()` with health endpoints at `GET /health` and `GET /internal/healthcheck`.

Run it with:

```bash
uv run python -m {{ package_name }} stream
```

Or expose the ASGI wrapper with uvicorn:

```bash
uv run uvicorn {{ package_name }}.runtimes.stream.app:build_asgi_app --factory
```

Configure Redis with `APP_REDIS_URL`.

The generated runtime subscribes to the Redis stream named by `APP_STREAM_PING_STREAM`.
{% endif %}

